-- Bayern Munich, Chelsea Play Extra Time in Champions League Final
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-05-19T20:40:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-19/bayern-munich-chelsea-play-extra-time-in-champions-league-final.html
Chelsea and  Bayern Munich  are going
to extra time tied 1-1 in the Champions Leaguee soccer final.  Chelsea’s Didier Drogba scored in the 88th minute to tie
the game at the  Allianz Arena  in Munich. The goal came five
minutes after Thomas Muller gave Bayern the lead.  The teams will play 30 extra minutes and then go to a
penalty shootout if the score remains tied.  Bayern Munich is looking to win Europe’s elite club
competition for a fifth time, while Chelsea seeks its first
title.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  